{"lemma":"دَرْسَيْ","slug":"دَرْسَيْ","root":"د.ر.س","root_slug":"د-ر-س","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ر-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَرْس","root":"درس","pos":"V","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12416","n12421","n12422"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to erase, to efface, to obliterate, to wipe out, to make hard to see"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to thresh, to flail","examples":[{"text":"وَأَمَّا المُصَنَّبُ فَيُؤْخَذُ الصِنَابُ الْحَدِيثُ وَيُجْتَنَبُ الْقَدِيمُ وَيُغْسَلُ حَبُّهُ بِالْمَاءِ الْعَذْبِ وَيُجَفَّفُ ثُمَّ يُدْرَسُ وَيُغَرْبَلُ ثُمَّ يُعْمَدُ إِلَى الْمُصْطَارِ الْحُلْوِ الْغَايَةِ فِي الْحَلَاوَةِ فَيُمْلِئ مِنْهُ خَابِيَةً وَيُقَسَّمُ ذٰلِكَ الصِنَابُ أَقْسَامًا ثَلَاثَةً وَيُجْعَلُ كُلُّ ثُلْثٍ فِي خَرِيطَةٍ وَيُرْبَطُ فِي قَصَبَةٍ مِثْلَ مَا تَقَدَّمَ وَيُذْرَى مِن ذٰلِكَ الصِنَابِ عَلَى وَجْهِ الْمُصْطَارِ فِي أَعْلَا الْخَابِيَةِ حَتَّى يُسْتَرَ وَيَنْعَقِدَ.","english":"In what concerns the mustard preparation, one takes new mustard, avoiding the old, and cleans its grains with sweet water and dries them, then one threshes and sieves it, thereafter puts it to must of utmost sweetness, and it fills from it a vessel, and this mustard is dealt into three portions, of which all thirds are transferred into a pouch tied up with a cane in the way said earlier, and from this mustard one sews onto the must’s surface in the upper part of the vessel until it is covered and thickens."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to study, to learn","examples":[{"text":"يَدْرُسُ ٱلْهَنْدَسَةَ فِي ٱلْجَامِعَةِ.","english":"He studies engineering at the university."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become erased, to become effaced, to become obliterated, to become wiped out, to become hard to see"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to teach, to educate","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَرَسَ (darasa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"study, studies"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lesson"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"class, class hour, period"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lecture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"relic, trace, mark (of a thing effaced)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tail"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"According to Geiger meanings of interpreting pettily much, the meaning “deuteln”, specifically in Qurʔān 6:105 and Qurʔān 6:156, are a semantic loan from Hebrew דָּרַשׁ (dāráš)."},"ipa":["/da.ra.sa/","/dar.ra.sa/","/dars/","/dirs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12416","headword_ar":"دَرَسَ","root":"drs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duruwsN","text_ar":"دُرُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a trace, or mark, or what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasomN","text_ar":"رَسْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, A, K, and a house, A, or a thing, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became effaced, erased, rased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Andrs","text_ar":"اندرس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) said of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rsm","text_ar":"رسم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the trace, or mark, of a house; or what remained, cleaving to the ground, marking the place of a house;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became covered with sand and dust blown over it by the wind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dvr","text_ar":"دثر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an abode, or a place of sojourning,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became effaced, erased, rased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated, and its traces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains, became concealed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unseen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darusa","text_ar":"دَرُسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa","text_ar":"دَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses explained above, but in an intensive manner. (M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=yaAtu","text_ar":"الا=يَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasati","text_ar":"دَارَسَتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as explained near the end of this paragraph.] ―         -b3-  Hence, also, (AHeyth,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa Alv~awobi","text_ar":"دَرَسَ الثَّوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, became old and worn out."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, S, A, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa AlkitaAbu","text_ar":"دَرَسَ الكِتَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The writing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"book, became old."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  [Hence, also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasato","text_ar":"دَرَسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duruwsN","text_ar":"دُرُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman, S, M, A, K, or, accord. to Lh, a girl, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"menstruated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasatohu Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"دَرَسَتْهُ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyaAHu","text_ar":"الرِّيَاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effaced, erased, rased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated, it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by repeatedly passing over it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) namely, a trace, or mark, [of a house &c.,] or what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasomN","text_ar":"رَسْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"erased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a house; (A;) or a thing: (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasahu Alqawomu","text_ar":"دَرَسَهُ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people effaced, erased, rased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated, it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (AHeyth,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa Alv~awoba","text_ar":"دَرَسَ الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rendered the garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, old and worn-out."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa","text_ar":"دَرَسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aEaAma","text_ar":"الطَّعَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHinoTapa","text_ar":"الحِنْطَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wanaHowahaA","text_ar":"وَنَحْوَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAsN","text_ar":"دِرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He trod,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrashed, the wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [because he who does so passes repeatedly over it:] of the dial. of El-Yemen: (M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAsN","text_ar":"دِرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense here indicated is of the dial. of Syria. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa AlmaroA^apa","text_ar":"دَرَسَ المَرْاَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAriyapa","text_ar":"الجَارِيَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He compressed the woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the girl."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"دَرَسَ النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trained, the she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A:) [and so, app., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasahaA","text_ar":"دَارَسَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for it is said that] the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudaArasapN","text_ar":"مُدَارَسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"training,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disciplining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a beast;] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returning time after time"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEah~udN","text_ar":"تَعَهُّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrN lamo yudorasu","text_ar":"بَعِيرٌ لَمْ يُدْرَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel that has not been ridden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b6-  Hence, (M,) [or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasatohu Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"دَرَسَتْهُ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa","text_ar":"دَرَسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~awoba","text_ar":"الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa AlkitaAba","text_ar":"دَرَسَ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAsapN","text_ar":"دِرَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAsapN","text_ar":"دَرَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAsN","text_ar":"دِرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He read the book;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he opposed it until it became easy for him to remember it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he read it repeatedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in order to remember it: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it easy to remember, by much reading:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he read and learned it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in vi. 105:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasahu","text_ar":"دَارَسَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudaArasapN","text_ar":"مُدَارَسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAsN","text_ar":"دِرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same: (M:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daras~ahu","text_ar":"دَرَسَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adorasahu","text_ar":"اَدْرَسَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the former of the last two has an intensive signification: the latter of them is mentioned by IJ: (TA:) [but accord. to the M, it is said by IJ that both of these are doubly trans., and have a different signification, which is also indicated in the A as that of the former of them: see 2:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkutuba","text_ar":"الكُتُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasato","text_ar":"دَارَسَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadaArasotuhaA","text_ar":"تَدَارَسْتُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aid~aArasotuhaA","text_ar":"اِدَّارَسْتُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", signify the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasotuhaA","text_ar":"دَرَسْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I read the books,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"read them repeatedly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquroA=na","text_ar":"القُرْا=نَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadaArasa","text_ar":"تَدَارَسَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He read the Kur-án, and returned to it time after time, in order that he might not forget it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasotu AlEiloma","text_ar":"دَرَسْتُ العِلْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diraAsapN","text_ar":"دِرَاسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I read science."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in the Kur [vi. 105], accord. to different reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waliyaquwluwA darasota","text_ar":"وَلِيَقُولُوا دَرَسْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasota","text_ar":"دَارَسْتَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And to the end that they may say, Thou hast read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] but some say that the former means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast read the books of the people of the Scriptures:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast consulted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conferred, with them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAkarotuhumo","text_ar":"ذَاكَرْتُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or the former means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast learned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás:) and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied, under the Jews as thy teachers, and they have read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied, under thee as their teacher:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, Mujáhid, K:) and another reading is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasa","text_ar":"دَارَسَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"page_break","n":871},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasa Aln~abiY~u Alyahuwda","text_ar":"دَارَسَ النَّبِىُّ اليَهُودَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he prophet hath read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied, with the Jews"},{"kind":"text","text":"] : and another, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasato","text_ar":"دَارَسَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which may be rendered in two ways:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Jews have read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consulted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conferred, with"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArasato","text_ar":"دَارَسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mohammad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The signs"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yaAt","text_ar":"ا=يَات"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have vied in length of time"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"antiquity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with those of other scriptures so that every one of them has for the most part become obliterated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and another reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasato","text_ar":"دَرَسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and another,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darusato","text_ar":"دَرُسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; both meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(these stories, or histories,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have become obliterated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are things which have long since passed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-' Abbás:) but the latter of these two verbs has a more intensive signification: and it is also said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They have been dissipated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darasa Ealayohi","text_ar":"دَرَسَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied, under him as his teacher;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^a Ealayohi","text_ar":"قَرَاَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb","AHeyth","S","A","M"]},{"entry_id":"n12421","headword_ar":"دَرْسٌ","root":"drs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, that is unapparent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as though the traces thereof had become effaced. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirosN","text_ar":"دِرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lecture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duruwsN","text_ar":"دُرُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12422","headword_ar":"دِرْسٌ","root":"drs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relic, trace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark, of a thing that becomes effaced, erased, rased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An old and worn-out garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K;) [app. an epithet used as a subst.;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"darosN","text_ar":"دَرْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dariysN","text_ar":"دَرِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, A, K;) ↓ which last also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an old and worn-out carpet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) ↓ and as an epithet, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old and worn-out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a coat of mail, (M, TA,) and to a sword, and to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"migofar","text_ar":"مِغْفَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]: (TA:) pl. [of the first]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraAsN","text_ar":"اَدْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) [a pl. of pauc.,] and [of the same or of either of the others]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirosaAnN","text_ar":"دِرْسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, K.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, or, as IF says, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayoD","text_ar":"الحَيْض"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw A^adoraAsK","text_ar":"اَبُو اَدْرَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u A^adoraAsK","text_ar":"اُمُّ اَدْرَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pudendum muliebre."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","K"]}]}}